{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771580401,"nonce":"Ue32u7BOGd4ASELexea2dTAFDss=","title":"Staff-created borrowers receive no notification email","message":"When staff creates a borrower via the Verwaltung UI, the borrower is added to the system with their personal data (name, email, phone) but receives no notification that an account was created for them.\n\nThis is a privacy concern - people's data is entered into the system without their knowledge or consent. At minimum, borrowers should receive an email informing them that an account was created, by whom, and for what purpose. Ideally this should include a link to accept the terms of service.\n\nNote: Self-registered borrowers already receive a confirmation email (confirm_email flow via email_token). Staff-created borrowers bypass this entirely.\n\nFound during Phase C integration testing.","files":null}]}